cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.EM, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-categories of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.EM (Embedded Systems), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper presents an automated, hardware-software co-designed, pipelined, high-throughput CNN inference framework on embedded heterogeneous system-on-chip (SoC) architectures, which involves hardware acceleration and optimization for CNN models. This work is relevant to the fields of hardware architecture, computer vision, embedded systems, systems and control, and neural computing.
